    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1195"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1195">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/6977.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of the Navy</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Navy Department</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 26, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your letter of the 23d instant, in which you request that a vessel be equipped
                    with an expeditionary force and sent to Topolobampo, Mexico, for the purpose of
                    affording protection for the American colony at Los Mochis.</p>
                <p>On the 24th instant the Commander-in-chief of the Pacific Fleet was directed to
                    embark at San Francisco a force of about 275 marines and to sail with the least
                    possible delay for Topolobampo. <pb facs="0967" n="851" xml:id="pg_851"/> The
                        <hi rend="italic">San Diego</hi> left San Francisco on the evening of the
                    25th instant, will stop at San Diego for an additional force, and should arrive
                    at Topolobampo about December second.</p>
                <p>Very sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Josephus Daniels.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
